{
  "texts": [
    "This method is capable of accurately extracting key molecular features from molecular embedding and features after dimensionality reduction, thus achieving a significant improvement in OI prediction performance on a single flavor dataset.",
    "Finally, in the frontier application of molecular graph generation, (Rivas et al. 2019b) applied DiffPool as an advanced adversarial pooling strategy for discriminators.",
    "By hierarchically aggregating nodes, DiffPool continuously optimizes the quality of graph embedding.",
    "This method not only facilitates the generation of high-quality molecular graphs but also greatly contributes to the innovation and development of graph generation models in the field of chemical design automation.",
    "In a wide range of applications in social networks, graph pooling methods demonstrate their unique advantages and flexibility, especially in core tasks such as Twitter topic modeling, detection of fake news on social platforms, analysis of dynamic social interactions, and Community question answering (CQA) systems."
  ]
}